HEADWORD: Aurichalcite
<hw>Au`ri*chal"cite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Aurichalceous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A hydrous
carbonate of copper and zinc, found in pale green or blue crystalline
aggregations. It yields a kind of brass on reduction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

